article.description: Jamaya Burr scored eight of his 26 points in overtime to help McNeese State beat Incarnate Word 79-76 on Monday night.
article.headline: Burr, McNeese State beat Incarnate Word 79-76 in OT
article.linkText: Burr, McNeese State beat Incarnate Word 79-76 in OT
article.story: LAKE CHARLES, La. -- Jamaya Burr scored eight of his 26 points in overtime to help McNeese State beat Incarnate Word 79-76 on Monday night. Burr scored McNeese State's first five points of overtime and added two free throws with 17 seconds left for a 76-73 lead. Mitchell Badillo answered with a layup but Tevin Jackson hit two free throws with seven seconds left to give McNeese State another three-point lead. Badillo and Burr both split a pair from the line in the closing seconds. James Harvey added 17 points for McNeese State (5-12, 3-4 Southland), which played its first overtime game of the season. Craig McFerrin had 14 points and Jackson added 12. Badillo led Incarnate Word (9-8, 4-2) with 21 points and Derail Green added 18 points with eight rebounds. Badillo hit two free throws with 1:22 left in the second half to tie it at 67 and neither team scored again to close regulation.
